  "bio": [
    "Jim Jannard founded sunglasses empire Oakley out of his car in 1975. His first product was a motorcycle grip that wicked sweat during long rides.",
    "It went public in 1995 and sold to Luxottica for $2.1 billion in cash in 2007.",
    "By then he was working on his next project, Red Digital, building high-resolution cameras used in movies like \"Avatar\" and \"The Hobbit.\"",
    "He launched Red Hydrogen One, a holographic smartphone, in Nov. 2018. It was plagued with issues, but he says the second version will be better."
  ],
  "about": [
    "The USC pharmacy student dropped out in the 1960s after clashing with professors over bringing his dog to class.",
    "Jannard named Oakley after his beloved English Setter, Oakley Anne. He has funded a breeder in Washington for three decades."
  ]
